Task 1:
-------

Obtain the details of all the active network interfaces on the machine. Then obtain the details of all the existing network interfaces on the machine.

Task 2:
-------

Obtain the IP address of the eth0 interface of the machine.

(Bonus task: What does the IP indicate? Hint: classes of IP addresses)

Task 3:
-------

Check how many virtual interfaces exist on the machine and deactivate the eth0:2 virtual interface and also verify if the interface is active.

Task 4:
-------

Now set the IP address of the eth0:2 to 10.2.48.121, activate it and verify  the IP assigned to it.
